.TH RSRCH 1 "November 2025" "1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rsrch \- Docker-based AI research automation tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rsrch
.I command
[
.I arguments
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rsrch
is a CLI wrapper for a Dockerized Perplexity.ai automation service. It manages the Docker containers and provides an interface for querying.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B start
Starts the Docker services (browser and API server) in the background.
.TP
.B stop
Stops the Docker services.
.TP
.B restart
Restarts the Docker services.
.TP
.B status
Shows the status of the Docker containers.
.TP
.B logs
Follows the logs of the Docker containers.
.TP
.B auth
Starts the authentication process.
.br
This will launch the browser service and the auth script. You must connect to \fBlocalhost:5900\fR using a VNC client to see the browser and log in manually.
.br
Once logged in, return to the terminal and press ENTER to save the session state to \fB./data/auth.json\fR.
.TP
.B query "\fIquestion\fR"
Sends a query to the running server via HTTP API.
.br
If the server is not running, it will attempt to start it.
.br
.B Example:
.br
.B rsrch query "What is the history of the internet?"\fR
.TP
.B notebook create "\fItitle\fR"
Creates a new NotebookLM notebook with the specified title.
.TP
.B notebook add-source "\fIurl\fR" [--notebook "\fItitle\fR"]
Adds a URL source to the active or specified notebook.
.TP
.B notebook audio [--notebook "\fItitle\fR"]
Generates an audio overview for the active or specified notebook.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /opt/rsrch/
Installation directory containing Docker configuration.
.TP
.B ./data/auth.json
File where authentication state (cookies) is saved.
.TP
.B ./data/results/
Directory where query results are saved.

